Focusing on the three pillars as a whole, we based our research on two papers that analyzed the alignment between sustainability and circular economy indicators (Kristensen and Mosgaard, 2020; de Oliveira et al., 2021) for nano and micro levels. The first paper analyzed thirty indicators, while the second analyzed fifty-eight. The two reached similar conclusions, including that few indicators align with sustainability (social, economic, and environmental pillars). Kristensen & Mosgaard (2020) research resulted in three indicators aligned with our proposal, all contemplated in de Oliveira et al. (2021) results. Thus, the indicators were selected from de Oliveira et al. (2021) results. The eight chosen indicators are listed below:

                           •

Sustainability Performance Indicators (SPI) (Mesa et al., 2018);


                           •

End of Life Best Practice Indicators (BPI) (Jiménez-Rivero and García-Navarro, 2016);


                           •

Sustainable Circular Index (SCI) (Azevedo et al., 2017);


                           •

Expended Zero Waste Practice Model (ZWP) (Veleva et al., 2017);


                           •

Set of Indicators to Assess Sustainability (SIAS) (Golinska et al., 2015);


                           •

Circular Business Model Set of Indicators based on Sustainability (CBM-IS) (Rossi et al., 2020);


                           •

Multi-Criteria Evaluation Method of Product-Level Circularity Strategies (MCEM-PLCS) (Alamerew et al., 2020);


                           •

Product Recovery Multi-Criteria Decision Tool (PR-MCDT) (Alamerew and Brissaud, 2019).

As for sustainability, the SDGs considered were SDG 6, SDG 7, SDG 8, SDG12, and SDG 15. According to Schroeder et al. (2019), those are the ones with the more direct contribution, and there is a strong relationship between CE practices and them. Moreover, they are related to the nano and micro levels. Thus, based on the targets directly affected by CE, the indicators should have referred to the following:

                              •

SDG 6: Water use reduction or efficiency, Amount of water recovered in the treatment, Employee hygiene conditions;


                              •

SDG 7: Energy use efficiency or cost, Renewable energy compared to fossil fuel, Equipment efficiency;


                              •

SDG 8: Production/productivity efficiency, Research, and development innovation/incentive, CE strategies efficiency, Job creation;


                              •

SDG 12: Energy and resource usage optimization, CE strategies, Waste generation minimization, gasses emission;


                              •

SDG 15: Water use optimization, Raw materials use reduction, Resources from deforestation or deforested areas.
